HEADWORD: Planipennia
<hw>Pla`ni*pen"ni*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. L. <ets>planus</ets> plane + <ets>penna</ets> wing.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A suborder of Neuroptera, including those that
have broad, flat wings, as the ant-lion, lacewing, etc. Called also
<altname>Planipennes</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Planipetalous</ent>⟦br⟧
